        Forty-eight hours—two days until I can leave.

        Go home—return to humanity, civilization, the bureaucratic system that sent me on the courier mission in the first place—leave this weird accidental plant community.

        Florence prompts, "Kira? What do you want Buddy to tell them?"

        «What do I want?»

        I tell Florence, "Tell them… I'm medically stable—being cared for by local inhabitants—transmitting coordinates now. Forty-eight hours works."

        Buddy sends the information. The freighter acknowledges and makes plans to extract one human survivor from the plant facility.

