        Florence smiles, "Well done, all of you."

        Scout bounces in celebration, but it's muted—confused celebration, a happy-sad bounce.

        Because Scout, at least, understands the complexity.

        I'm standing in this facility I've started thinking of as home, surrounded by plants who've become my community, and I should be celebrating that I can finally leave—yet I feel hollow.

