        When I frame it like that, the choice feels… obvious.

        But it shouldn't be obvious — I'm human, and humans should want to be with humans, right?

        Except… when did human systems ever make me feel valued? I was courier pilot three eight four seven, a replaceable cog in a bureaucratic machine. Here, I'm Kira — my voice shapes community decisions.

